8785	[Injective resolutions provide enough injectives]
8786	  \label{lem:enoughInjectives_of_hasInjectiveResolutions}
8787	  \lean{AlgebraicGeometry.enoughInjectives_of_hasInjectiveResolutions}
8788	  \uses{lem:right_derived_injective_resolution}
8789	  An abelian category equipped with chosen injective resolutions has enough injectives: every object
8790	  admits a monomorphism into an injective object.
8791	\end{lemma}
8792	\begin{proof}
8793	  \uses{lem:right_derived_injective_resolution}
8794	  Given an object \(X\), take its chosen injective resolution \(X \to \mathcal{I}^\bullet\). The
8795	  degree-\(0\) term \(\mathcal{I}^0\) is injective and the resolution's unit \(X \to \mathcal{I}^0\) is
8796	  a monomorphism, so it is an injective presentation of \(X\). As every object has one, the category
8797	  has enough injectives.
8798	\end{proof}
